Code Unknown;;2000;;Not Rated;;Drama;;7.2;;Michael Haneke;;Juliette Binoche,Thierry Neuvic,Josef Bierbichler,Alexandre Hamidi,Maimouna Hélène Diarra,Ona Lu Yenke,Djibril Kouyaté,Luminita Gheorghiu,Crenguta Hariton,Bob Nicolescu,Bruno Todeschini,Paulus Manker,Didier Flamand,Walid Afkir,Maurice Bénichou,Carlo Brandt,Philippe Demarle,Marc Duret;;Jean, a farm lad, wants to escape his silent father; he runs to Paris to his older brother, Georges, who's away covering the war in Kosovo. Angry, he throws a bag of half-eaten pastry into a beggar's lap. Amadou, a young Franco-African, berates him. The police arrive, arrest Amadou and deport the beggar. Georges's girlfriend Anne is upset; it colors her relationship with Georges when he returns from the war. Separate lives intersect for the one moment, around the pastry bag, and all are altered. We follow each as repercussions of the incident play out. Deaf children bookend the film pantomiming words, feelings, and situations: what they are expressing?;;https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0216625/